  Dialogue:
  - Do you really think prayers work?
  - When I was young I didn't believe it. I thought that humans had invented a god
    who was a powerful human simply because we are sociable animals, our minds evolved
    precisely to have the ability to communicate with other humans.
  - "So it seemed obvious to me that <color=#FF0080>Shu\xE1</color> was a false god
    created by human imagination."
  - But one day I contracted the blue plague. What I hated most was not the disease
    but the treatment. The medications made my body boil and I had to keep taking
    them for months.
  - I wanted to give up several times, I thought dying from the plague would be much
    better, at least I would have a peaceful death. And even if I took all the meds
    I would only have a one in five chance of surviving.
  - "I was tired, ready to give up. And when I reached the deepest despair, I felt
    Shu\xE1 by my side, in that moment I felt that I was not alone, in that moment
    I knew that something greater was protecting and guiding me."
  - At that moment I knew that I would have the strength to defeat the blue plague.
  - "Why didn't <color=#FF0080>Shu\xE1</color> protect the four out of five people
    who underwent treatment and died?"
  - I don't know, and maybe he doesn't exist, maybe what I felt at that time was
    just an illusion.
  - But I guarantee you that if I hadn't believed him I would be dead by now.
  - Whether he exists or not, it was my belief in him that saved me not just from
    the plague, but from the despair and agony of facing death head-on, and for that
    I will always be grateful to him.
  - "Your story is beautiful <color=#FF0080>Kain</color>, if you are alive thanks
    to <color=#FF0080>Shu\xE1</color> I will also thank him."
  - The two prayed together in silence.
  DialogueBR:
  - "Voc\xEA realmente acha que as ora\xE7\xF5es funcionam?"
  - "Eu n\xE3o acreditava quando era jovem. Eu pensei que as pessoas tinham inventado
    um deus que fosse um humano poderoso simplesmente porque somos animais soci\xE1veis,
    nossas mentes evolu\xEDram justamente para termos a habilidade de nos comunicarmos
    com outros humanos."
  - "Ent\xE3o me parecia \xF3bvio que <color=#FF0080>Shu\xE1</color> era um falso
    deus criado pela imagina\xE7\xE3o humana."
  - "Mas um dia eu contra\xED a peste azul. O que eu mais odiava n\xE3o era a doen\xE7a,
    mas o tratamento. Os medicamentos fizeram meu corpo ferver e tive que continuar
    os tomando por meses."
  - "Eu quis desistir v\xE1rias vezes, achei que morrer da peste seria muito melhor,
    pelo menos eu teria uma morte tranquila. E mesmo que eu tomasse todos os rem\xE9dios,
    s\xF3 teria uma chance em cinco de sobreviver."
  - "Eu estava cansado, pronto para desistir. E quando cheguei ao desespero mais
    profundo, senti Shu\xE1 ao meu lado, naquele momento senti que n\xE3o estava
    sozinho, naquele momento soube que algo maior estava me protegendo e me guiando."
  - "Naquele momento eu soube que teria for\xE7as para derrotar a praga azul."
  - "Por que o <color=#FF0080>Shu\xE1</color> n\xE3o protegeu as quatro em cada cinco
    pessoas que passaram pelo tratamento e morreram?"
  - "N\xE3o sei, talvez ele n\xE3o exista, talvez o que eu senti naquele momento
    fosse apenas uma ilus\xE3o."
  - "Mas garanto a voc\xEA que, se eu n\xE3o tivesse acreditado nele, j\xE1 estaria
    morto."
  - "Ele existindo ou n\xE3o, foi minha cren\xE7a nele que me salvou n\xE3o apenas
    da praga, mas do desespero e da agonia de enfrentar a morte de frente, e por
    isso sempre serei grato a ele."
  - "Sua hist\xF3ria \xE9 bela <color=#FF0080>Kain</color>, se voc\xEA est\xE1 vivo
    gra\xE7as ao <color=#FF0080>Shu\xE1</color> eu tamb\xE9m agradecerei a ele."
  - "Os dois rezaram juntos em sil\xEAncio."
